   </info>
   <refnamediv>
       <refname>studentize</refname>
               <refpurpose>studentize a ts, a vector or a matrix </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>[t]=studentize(x)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
<listitem><para>*  <term> x </term> =    a vector or matrix </para></listitem>
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
<listitem><para>*  <term> t </term> =    transformed matrix or ts</para></listitem>
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
If x is a vector or a ts, substract its mean and divide by its standard deviation. If x is a matrix, do the above for each column. 

        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>EXAMPLE</title>
              <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
load(GROCERDIR+'/data/bdhenderic.dat')
y=studentize(lm1)

               ]]></programlisting>
        </refsection>
 
